SLURM scripts for running benchmarks on a GPU cluster.

run-sbatch
    sbatch job script. Compiles, runs benchmark, saves CSV to results/<job_id>/.

submit
    Helper to submit from a local machine through an SSH proxy.

    Required env vars:
        PROXY_HOST   - SSH proxy/bastion hostname
        REMOTE_DIR   - path to the project on the cluster

    Optional:
        CLUSTER_HOST - if the cluster login node differs from the proxy
        PARTITION    - SLURM partition (default: gpu)
        ACCOUNT      - SLURM account
        MAX_N        - max limb count for benchmark sweep (default: 1048576)
        ITERS        - benchmark iterations (default: 5)
        WARMUP       - warmup runs (default: 2)

    Example:
        PROXY_HOST=bastion.example.com REMOTE_DIR=~/bigmul ./script/submit
        PROXY_HOST=bastion CLUSTER_HOST=gpu-login REMOTE_DIR=/scratch/$USER/bigmul ./script/submit
